COMPILING AND RUNNING AN AGENT IMPLEMENTATION IN SCALA

1.) In order to compile your Scala agent, setup the following layout in your
    Simple Build Tool (sbt):
	
    src/
       main/
          java/
             ModelDataTypes.java
          scala/
             SmartAgent.scala
    target/

    Use the "ModelDataTypes.java" and "SmartAgent.scala" from the "AgentScala" 
	folder of AbstractSwarm and start implementing your Scala-agent in 
	"src/main/scala/SmartAgent.scala".			 
    
	After implementing your Scala code, just run the sbt task "package" to
	create a corresponding .jar file.
		
2.) Add to the "AgentScala" folder of AbstractSwarm the following two files:
    - The SmartAgent.jar-file resulting from your "package" task (can be found
      in the "target" folder)
    - scala-library.jar (part of the Scala distribution)

3.) Start AbstractSwarm, open a scenario graph and select the "AgentScala"
    from "Agents" menu. Run the scenario.